# However we want to see correlation in graphical representation so below is function for that
def plot_corr(df, size=12):
    corr = df.corr()
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(size, size))
    ax.matshow(corr)
    plt.xticks(range(len(corr.columns)), corr.columns)
    plt.yticks(range(len(corr.columns)), corr.columns)
    plt.xticks(rotation = 90)
    for (i, j), z in np.ndenumerate(corr):
        ax.text(j, i, '{:0.4f}'.format(z), ha='center', va='center')

In [41]:
def draw_cm( actual, predicted ):
    cm = confusion_matrix( actual, predicted, [1,0] )
    sns.heatmap(cm, annot=True,  fmt='.2f', xticklabels = ["Loan", "NoLoan"] , yticklabels = ["Loan", "No Loan"] )
    plt.ylabel('True label')
    plt.xlabel('Predicted label')
    plt.show()

6. Give conclusion related to the Business understanding of your model?¶

The model created performed well on the test data with accuracy of 94% and a weighted average Recall of 0.94. Which is a significant jump from their previous success ratio.

As per the EDA analysis, there is a high correlation with Income (0.5025), CC Avg (0.3669) and CD Account (0.3164). Targetting those customer will increase the chance of sellign Personal Loan account and at the same time this will bring down the Marketing campaing cost as we are approaching specific class of customers.
